  "prompt": "How long does weed stay in your blood?",
  "response": "The length of time that marijuana (weed) remains detectable in your blood depends on several factors, including the frequency of use, the potency of the marijuana, your metabolism, and your body fat percentage. Here's a general guideline:\n\n- **Occasional users**: For someone who uses marijuana infrequently, THC (the psychoactive component of marijuana) can typically be detected in the blood for 1-3 days after use.\n- **Frequent users**: For regular users, THC can be detected in the blood for up to 7-10 days after the last use.\n\nThese time frames are approximate and can vary from person to person. Blood tests are less common for detecting marijuana use compared to urine tests, but they are more accurate in determining recent use.",
